title: Get ready to take to the skies in Westjet’s ‘Frozen’ themed plane (VIDEO)
text:
Get ready to take to the skies in Westjet’s ‘Frozen’ themed plane (VIDEO) Monday October 19, 2015 Print Article 
WestJet has added a ‘Frozen’ inspired airplane to its fleet of aircraft as can be seen in this Twitter picture. TORONTO, Oct 19 — Looks like people still aren’t ready to “Let It Go” which is why we now have a “Frozen” themed airplane courtesy of Canadian airline company WestJet 
The mostly-blue plane features Anna and Elsa working some snow magic on the tail, while snowman Olaf features on the front, lying under an umbrella on the beach. 
Disney artists and cast members collaborated with WestJet to design the Boeing 737 and it took the painting crew 21 days of 12-hour rotations to finish the paint job. 
The plane’s interior also got a makeover, featuring decals and headrest covers that follow the exterior’s cold-to-warm theme. 
This is the second Disney-themed aircraft to join WestJet’s fleet following the “Magic” plane that featured Sorcerer Mickey from the 1940 Disney classic “Fantasia” that was unveiled in 2013.
